<promed@promedmail.org>
[The usual role of fleas in transmission of plague from rodents to humans
is not mentioned in this article. Direct transmission via aerosol or
contact with skin abrasions is possible if humans are butchering marmots. I
recommend that interested persons review the background postings cited
above for the year 2000. - Mod.ES
[It would be appreciated if a reader with data confirming that bites of
marmots have resulted in cases of human plague sends us these data.
Transmission of plague to humans has been reported following both cat bites
and cat scratches. - Man. Ed. DS
